issue.title: Environment Support
issue.body:
Do we want to continue supporting long dead environments such as 5 year old versions of WebKit and IE6?

If so do we want to have a compatibility build and a modern build as lodash currently does?

comment.body: Lodash v4 is modern. The current and next to current release of Chrome, Firefox, Safari and & IE >= 9 (We have no IE9 or IE10 fixes so get it for free). With [MS dropping support for IE < 11](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/WindowsForBusiness/End-of-IE-support) that's a fine bar to set. Those still needing older environment support can supplement with ES5-shim and, optionally, ES6-shim.
